<h4 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-left" style="padding-top:0;padding-bottom:0">1. Submit a Request for Appraisal</h4>

<p class="has-text-align-left has-kubio-color-6-color has-text-color has-link-color" style="padding-top:0;padding-right:0;padding-bottom:0;padding-left:0">Start by providing key details about the property or item for appraisal. Use our online form or contact us directly, including as much information as possible for accuracy.</p>

<h4 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-left">2. Schedule the Appraisal </h4>

<p class="has-text-align-left has-kubio-color-6-color has-text-color has-link-color">Once we receive your request, our team will reach out to coordinate a convenient time for your appraisal.  Well accommodate your schedule to make the process seamless. </p>

<h4 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-left">3. Appraisal Report Preparation</h4>

<p class="has-text-align-left has-kubio-color-6-color has-text-color has-link-color">Our experts will analyze the information gathered during the appraisal process. Using advanced methodologies and industry standards, we craft a detailed and thorough report. This document will include all critical data, insights, and valuation metrics, providing you with everything you need for your next steps.</p>

<h4 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-left">4. Receive Your Appraisal Report</h4>

<p class="has-text-align-left has-kubio-color-6-color has-text-color has-link-color">After the appraisal is completed, well promptly deliver your report. You can choose how you&#8217;d like to receive itvia email, physical mail, or through a secure online portal. Were here to answer any questions and help you interpret the findings if needed.</p>
